gnome-power-manager: gnome-power-manager
gnome-power-manager:
gnome-power-manager: GNOME Power Manager is a GNOME session daemon that
gnome-power-manager: acts as a policy agent on top of the Project Utopia
gnome-power-manager: stack, which includes the kernel, hotplug, udev, and
gnome-power-manager: HAL. GNOME Power Manager listens for HAL events and
gnome-power-manager: responds with user-configurable reactions. Currently it
gnome-power-manager: supports UPS's, laptop batteries and AC adapters. Its
gnome-power-manager: goal is to be architecture neutral and free of polling
gnome-power-manager: and other hacks.
